    &lt;Title&gt;Recent Hand Surgery&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Harry&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I recently had surgery on my hand, to release a long standing &amp;amp;quot;trigger finger&amp;amp;quot; problem.  I received a consultant appointment within a matter of days of being referred by my GP.  There was a clear discussion about the options available to me, including risks &amp;amp;amp; benefits.  

The actual operation was as much fun as these things can be (!) but totally professional in all aspects - preparation; the operation; the immediate after care.  I left with all of the information that I needed to take care of my wound during the period needed to fully heal and a follow-up appointment, that had been made whilst I was in the immediate recovery area.

I have had a completely positive experience here and I have confidence that my follow-up appointment will hit the same high standards.

Thanks v much&lt;/CommentText&gt;
